<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
The specific epithet honours the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ye’kwana">Ye'kwana</normalizedToken>
, indigenous people from the Roraima State, Brazil. The name is to be regarded as a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
